  notipulse: {
    name: 'NotiPulse',
    author: 'chef',
    slug: 'notipulse',
    tags: ['bold', 'clean', 'dashboard', 'light', 'mobile-app'],
    content: `# NotiPulse Design System

## Overview

NotiPulse is an alert-driven, card-based design system built for notification-heavy and alert management apps. It prioritizes glanceable information with bold severity colors, prominent card surfaces that lift on alert, and a clear visual hierarchy that enables rapid triage. The system uses material shadows and animated elevation changes to convey urgency. Every pattern is designed so users can scan, prioritize, and act on notifications within seconds.

---

## Colors

- **Primary** (#EF4444): Red -- urgent alerts, critical notifications
- **Secondary** (#3B82F6): Blue -- informational, system messages
- **Tertiary** (#F59E0B): Amber -- warnings, attention required
- **Background** (#F9FAFB): Page background
- **Surface** (#FFFFFF): Notification cards, panels
- **Success** (#22C55E): Resolved alerts, acknowledged
- **Warning** (#F59E0B): Warning-level alerts, pending
- **Error** (#EF4444): Critical alerts, failures
- **Info** (#3B82F6): System updates, informational

## Typography

- **Headline Font**: Albert Sans
- **Body Font**: Inter
- **Mono Font**: Source Code Pro

- **Display**: Albert Sans 30px bold, 38px line height
- **Headline**: Albert Sans 24px bold, 32px line height
- **Subhead**: Albert Sans 19px semibold, 28px line height
- **Body Large**: Inter 16px regular, 26px line height
- **Body**: Inter 14px regular, 22px line height
- **Body Small**: Inter 13px regular, 20px line height
- **Caption**: Inter 12px medium, 18px line height
- **Overline**: Inter 11px semibold, 16px line height
- **Code**: Source Code Pro 13px regular, 20px line height

---

## Spacing

- **Base unit:** 6px
- **Scale:** 6 / 12 / 18 / 24 / 30 / 36 / 48 / 60 / 72
- **Component padding:** 12px (compact) | 18px (default) | 24px (relaxed)
- **Section spacing:** 36px between major sections, 18px between notification groups
- **Alert cards:** 18px internal padding, 12px between stacked cards

## Border Radius

- **None** (0px): Full-width status bars, edge dividers
- **Small** (6px): Severity badges, inline chips
- **Medium** (12px): Notification cards, inputs
- **Large** (16px): Modals, bottom sheets
- **XL** (20px): Expanded alert panels
- **Full** (9999px): Pill filters, avatar circles, counters

## Elevation

Material shadows with dynamic elevation for alert states.
- **Subtle**: Layered shadow: 1px vertical with 3px blur at 6% opacity plus 1px vertical with 2px blur at 4% opacity, both black. Resting cards.
- **Medium**: Layered shadow: 4px vertical with 8px blur at 8% opacity plus 2px vertical with 4px blur at 4% opacity, both black. Active notification cards.
- **Large**: Layered shadow: 12px vertical with 24px blur at 12% opacity plus 4px vertical with 8px blur at 6% opacity, both black. Alerted cards (lifted).
- **Overlay**: Deep 20px vertical, 48px blur, black at 18% opacity. Full-screen overlays.
- **Alert Lift**: Colored 8px vertical, 20px blur, red (#EF4444) at 15% opacity. Critical alert card elevation.

## Components

### Buttons

- **Primary**: Red (#EF4444) fill, white (#FFFFFF) text, no border. Press darkens to #DC2626.
- **Secondary**: White (#FFFFFF) fill, blue (#3B82F6) text, 1px blue (#3B82F6) border. Press tints the background to light blue (#EFF6FF).
- **Ghost**: Transparent fill, gray (#6B7280) text, no border. Press fills with #F3F4F6.
- **Destructive**: Dark red (#B91C1C) fill, white (#FFFFFF) text, no border. Press darkens to #991B1B.

Available in small (34px tall, 12px padding), medium (44px tall, 16px padding), and large (52px tall, 20px padding). Disabled buttons drop to 0.4 opacity with no press feedback. All interactive elements maintain a minimum 44px touch target.

### Cards

- **Default**: White (#FFFFFF) background with a 1px #E5E7EB border, 12px rounded corners, 18px padding, and a subtle shadow at rest.
- **Elevated (Alerted)**: White (#FFFFFF) background with a 4px left border in the relevant semantic color, 12px rounded corners, 18px padding, and a large shadow. Alert cards animate from subtle to large shadow on new notification arrival over 300ms ease-out. The severity stripe on the left enables quick scanning.

### Inputs

Inputs have a minimum height of 44px.

In the default state the border is #E5E7EB on a white (#FFFFFF) background with no shadow. On hover the border strengthens to #D1D5DB. On focus the border turns blue (#3B82F6) over a white (#FFFFFF) background with a 3px blue ring at 12% opacity. In the error state the border turns red (#EF4444) over a light red (#FEF2F2) background with a 3px red ring at 10% opacity. When disabled the border fades to #F3F4F6 on a light (#F9FAFB) background.

Labels are 13px medium (500) in text-primary with 6px spacing below. Helper text is 12px in text-secondary; error helper uses the error color.

### Chips

- **Filter**: Light gray (#F3F4F6) fill, dark gray (#374151) text, pill-shaped, 6px 14px padding, toggleable with primary red background when active.
- **Status**: Semantic color at 12% opacity fill, semantic-colored text, pill-shaped, 4px 12px padding. Priority chips map as follows: CRITICAL = red, HIGH = amber, MEDIUM = blue, LOW = gray.

### Lists

Each row is at least 64px tall (accommodating title and description preview) with 12px 18px padding, separated by a 1px #F3F4F6 divider inset by 18px. Press feedback fills the background with #F3F4F6 after 100ms. Unread rows show a 3px red (#EF4444) left border, bold title text, and a faint red (#FFFBFB) background. Read rows have no left border, regular-weight text, and the standard background. Swipe left to dismiss/archive, swipe right to snooze.

### Checkboxes

20px square with 6px rounded corners. Unchecked state has a 2px #D1D5DB border on a transparent background. When checked the box fills red (#EF4444) with a white checkmark. Indeterminate state fills red (#EF4444) with a white dash for batch selection. Focus adds a 3px red ring at 15% opacity. Touch target is 44px. Disabled drops to 0.35 opacity.

### Radio Buttons

20px circular. Unselected state has a 2px #D1D5DB border on a transparent background. When selected the border turns 2px red (#EF4444) with a 10px red inner dot. Focus adds a 3px red ring at 15% opacity. Touch target is 44px. Disabled drops to 0.35 opacity.

### Tooltips

Dark (#111827) background with white (#FFFFFF) text in Inter 13px regular (400), 10px rounded corners, 8px 14px padding, and a 6px arrow matching the background. Maximum width is 220px. Shows after 300ms on long-press (mobile) and hides after 100ms.

---

## Do's and Don'ts

1. **Do** use severity-colored left borders on notification cards for instant visual triage.
2. **Do** animate card elevation when a new alert arrives to draw attention without being disruptive.
3. **Don't** use the primary red color for non-alert UI elements -- reserve it for urgency.
4. **Do** display timestamps in relative format ("2m ago") for glanceability.
5. **Don't** stack more than 3 unread critical alerts before prompting the user to triage.
6. **Do** support batch actions (select all, dismiss selected, snooze selected) for efficiency.
7. **Don't** auto-dismiss critical alerts -- always require explicit user acknowledgment.
8. **Do** group notifications by source or severity with clear section headers.
9. **Don't** play sound or haptic for every notification level -- reserve strong feedback for critical alerts only.
10. **Do** provide a clear "mark all as read" action accessible within one tap.`,
  },
